)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@@@@@]@D@A@]                      DMAAC/1108 COPY-DUMP PROCEWL
)@@G@@SSOR  @D@@@A                      DMAAC/1100 COPY-DUMP PROCESSOR  @E@A@]WM
)@@G@@                    MODIFIED BY OFFICE OF COMPUTER SCIENCE  @D@@@A      WN
)@@G@@               MODIFIED BY BUREAU OF PUBLIC DEBT@D@A@]                  WO
)@@G@@       TECHNICAL SERVICES BRANCH    @B@A@]                              WP
)@@G@@ LEVEL 03D  @B@@@A                               LEVEL 03H  @@@@@]@@@@@]WQ
)@@G@@@^@@@]    I.  INTRODUCTION    @@@@@]@G@A@]        A  REVISED  VERSION OFWR
)@@G@@ 'COPY-DUMP',  CPD LEVEL 03D,  IS NOW     @F@@@A        A  REVISED  VERSWS
)@@G@@ION OF 'COPY-DUMP',  CPD LEVEL 3H,  IS NOW@G@A@]    AVAILABLE ON THE UNIWT
)@@G@@VAC 1108 SYSTEM.  THIS NEW VERSION CONTAINS     @G@@@A    AVAILABLE ON TWU
)@@G@@HE UNIVAC 1100 SYSTEM.  THIS NEW VERSION CONTAINS     @G@@@]    FEATURESWV
)@@G@@  NOT  PREVIOUSLY AVAILABLE IN CPD.   SOME CPD FEATURES     @G@@@]    ARWW
)@@G@@E  AVAILABLE  IN 'FURPUR' BUT ARE INCLUDED IN CPD TO PRESERVE     @G@@@]WX
)@@G@@    CONTINUITY. CPD IS STILL INTENDED TO BE USED AS A SUPPLEMENT TO     WY
)@@G@@@C@@@]    FURPUR AND NOT AS A REPLACEMENT FOR IT.     @@@@@]@G@@@]      WZ
)@@G@@  AS  THIS  IS  AN  AUXILIARY  PROCESSOR,   COPY-DUMP  IS NOT     @G@@@]XA
)@@G@@    SUPPORTED BY UNIVAC SYSTEM'S SOFTWARE, AND THEREFORE SHOULD NOT     XB
)@@G@@@G@@@]    BE  USED  IN PRODUCTION PROGRAMS.   FURPUR ON THE OTHER HAND IXC
)@@G@@S     @G@@@]    CONTINUOUSLY  MONITERED AND ENHANCED BY UNIVAC.   SHOULDXD
)@@G@@ UNIVAC     @G@@@]    SOFTWARE ACQUIRE THE ADDITIONAL CAPABILITIES OF THXE
)@@G@@IS PROCESSOR,     @E@@@]    COPY-DUMP MAY BE REMOVED FROM THE OPERATING XF
)@@G@@SYSTEM.     @@@@@]@@@@@]@^@@@]    II.  MAJOR USES     @@@@@]@@@@@]@ @@@]XG
)@@G@@    A.  TAPE MANIPULATION     @@@@@]@G@@@]        ONE  FUNCTION  OF CPD XH
)@@G@@IS TO PRINT,  DUPLICATE,  AND COMPARE     @G@@@]    TAPES.    IT  HAS  BXI
)@@G@@EEN  FOUND PARTICULARLY USEFUL IN ACCESSING     @G@@@]    UNKNOWN TAPES XJ
)@@G@@(I.E. THOSE THE CONTENTS OF WHICH THE USER HAS NO     @G@@@]    KNOWLEDGXK
)@@G@@E).    IT  IS  ALSO USEFUL IN DUPLICATING AND COMPARING     @G@@@]    TAXL
)@@G@@PES,   DOING A STRAIGHTFORWARD DUPLICATION OF A TAPE AND THEN     @G@@@]XM
)@@G@@    INFORMING  THE  USER  OF  HOW  WELL  THE  JOB  WAS  DONE.   THE     XN
)@@G@@@G@@@]    COMPARISON  PROCESSES RECORD BY RECORD,  PRINTING OUT THE FIRSXO
)@@G@@T     @B@@@]    NON-COMPARING RECORD FROM BOTH TAPES. @@@@@]@A@@@]    B.XP
)@@G@@  FASTRAND DRUM MANIPULATION  @@@@@]@G@@@]        SOME CPD COMMANDS WILLXQ
)@@G@@ HANDLE BOTH TAPE AND FASTRAND FILES.     @G@@@]    THEY ARE:  1.) PRT-PXR
)@@G@@RINT, 2.) PSB- POSITION BACKWARDS, 3.) PSE-     @G@@@]    POSITION SHORTXS
)@@G@@ OF END OF FILE,  4.) PSF - POSITION FORWARD, AND     @G@@@]    5.) FRE XT
)@@G@@- FREE A FILE.  THE DUP (DUPLICATE) COMMAND WILL DUPE A     @G@@@]    TAXU
)@@G@@PE  FILE  TO  FASTRAND,  BUT WILL NOT DUPE A FASTRAND FILE TO     @B@@@]XV
)@@G@@    TAPE OR A FASTRAND TO A FASTRAND FILE.@@@@@]@ @@@]    C.  MULTIFILE XW
)@@G@@CAPABILITY  @@@@@]@G@@@]         CPD  ALLOWS THE  PROCESSING OF MULTIFILXX
)@@G@@E  TAPES.   THROUGH     @G@@@]    THE USE OF THE  'F'  OPTION, MULTIFILEXY
)@@G@@ DUPES, COMPARES, PRINTS,     @G@@@]    AND POSITIONINGS MAY BE PROCESSEXZ
)@@G@@D. ALL COMMANDS BUT TEF WORK WITH   @G@@@]    THE 'F' OPTION,  BUT CAUTIYA
)@@G@@ON SHOULD BE USED.   IF IT IS DESIRED     @G@@@]    TO  SPECIFY  RECORDSYB
)@@G@@  CPD MUST BE REINITIALIZED WITHOUT THE 'F'     @G@@@]    OPTION  BECAUSYC
)@@G@@E  THE  F  OPTION CAUSES N TO BE INTERPRETED AS N     @G@@@]    NUMBER  YD
)@@G@@OF  EOF  MARKS  TO  MOVE  PAST  RATHER THAN N NUMBER OF     @]@@@]    REYE
)@@G@@CORDS.@@@@@]@@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]    III.  CONTROL CARD AND OPTIONS  @@@@@]YF
)@@G@@@@@@@]@G@@@]        THE  CPD  PROCESSOR  MUST BE CALLED INTO CORE BEFOREYG
)@@G@@ IT CAN     @A@@@]    PROCESS ANY COPY-DUMP COMMANDS. @G@@@]        THE YH
)@@G@@COPY-DUMP PROCESSOR IS CALLED BY THE FOLLOWING COMMAND:     @@@@@]@C@@@]YI
)@@G@@             @CPD,OPTIONS    (NO BLANKS ALLOWED)@@@@@]@G@@@]    THE  OPTYJ
)@@G@@IONS  ON  THE  @CPD  CARD  TELL  THE CPD PROCESSOR WHAT     @G@@@]    FOYK
)@@G@@RMAT(S)  (OCTAL,   ALPHABETIC,   ETC.)  TO USE WHEN DOING ANY     @G@@@]YL
)@@G@@    REQUESTED PRINTING,  WHETHER THE FILES ON THE COPY-DUMP COMMAND     YM
)@@G@@@G@@@]    CARDS  WHICH  FOLLOW ARE DRUM OR TAPE,  AND WHETHER ANY NUMBERYN
)@@G@@S     @G@@@]    SPECIFIED  ON THE COMMAND CARDS ARE TO BE INTERPRETED ASYO
)@@G@@ RECORD     @G@@@]    COUNTS  OR  FILE  COUNTS.   THE  OPTIONS APPLY TO YP
)@@G@@ALL COPY-DUMP     @G@@@]    COMMANDS  FOLLOWING  THE  @CPD  CARD.    IF YQ
)@@G@@ YOU WANT TO CHANGE     @G@@@]    OPTIONS  SUCH AS FROM FILES (F) TO DRUYR
)@@G@@M (D) YOU MUST RECALL THE     @G@@@]    CPD PROCESSOR WITH THE DESIRED OYS
)@@G@@PTIONS.  COPY-DUMP ALSO MUST BE     @G@@@]    RECALLED  WHEN  NON-COPY-DYT
)@@G@@UMP  COMMANDS ARE INTERMIXED WITH THE     @A@@@]    CPD COMMANDS IN THE YU
)@@G@@RUNSTREAM.  @@@@@]@@@@@]@B@@@]      OPTIONS AVAILABLE ON THE @CPD CARD: YV
)@@G@@@@@@@]@@@@@]@E@@@]         A - PRINT ALL RECORDS IN ALPHA, DIVIDED INTO YW
)@@G@@WORDS.@@@@@]@G@@@]         H - PRINT  ALL  RECORDS  IN ALPHA,  NOT DIVIDYX
)@@G@@ED INTO WORDS     @B@@@]             (CONTINUOUS CHARACTERS).     @@@@@]YY
)@@G@@@G@@@]         Q - PRINT ALL RECORDS IN ALPHA (ASCII), DIVIDED INTO WORDYZ
)@@G@@S.    @@@@@]@G@@@]         R - PRINT  ALL  RECORDS  IN ALPHA (ASCII),  NZA
)@@G@@OT DIVIDED INTO   @B@@@]             (CONTINUOUS CHARACTERS).     @@@@@]ZB
)@@G@@@G@@@]         O - PRINT  ALL RECORDS IN OCTAL,  DIVIDED INTO WORDS (THIZC
)@@G@@S     @G@@@]             IS  THE  LETTER 'O',  NOT A ZERO) (THIS IS THE ZD
)@@G@@DEFAULT     @E@@@]             PRINT FORMAT IF NO OPTIONS ARE SPECIFIED)ZE
)@@G@@.     @@@@@ @G@@@          P - PRINT ALL BLOCKS IN ERROR THEN DOING A COZF
)@@G@@MPARE. DEFAULT    @F@@@              - DEMAND - DON'T PRINT ANY BLOCKS. ZG
)@@G@@BATCH - PRINT THE @B@@@              FIRST 10 BLOCKS IN ERROR.    @@@@@]ZH
)@@G@@@G@@@]         X - SAMPLE  PRINT:   THE FIRST LINE OF EACH RECORD WILL BZI
)@@G@@E     @D@@@]             PRINTED IN THE PRINT FORMAT(S) SPECIFIED.@F@^@]ZJ
)@@G@@             THIS OPTION DOES NOT APPLY TO ASCII FORMATS Q AND R. @@@@@]ZK
)@@G@@@G@@@]         D - CONSIDER  ALL FILES REFERENCED AS DRUM FILES (WITH ONZL
)@@G@@E     @G@@@]             EXCEPTION  -  SEE  DUPLICATE  FUNCTION)  AND HAZM
)@@G@@NDLE IN     @ @@@]             SECTOR MULTIPLES.@@@@@]@G@@@]         F -ZN
)@@G@@ HANDLE  ALL  COUNTERS  GIVEN  ON COMMAND CARDS AS FILE     @G@@@]      ZO
)@@G@@       COUNTS  INSTEAD  OF RECORD COUNTS.   IF THIS OPTION IS     @G@@@]ZP
)@@G@@             SPECIFIED,   A  COUNTER VALUE MUST BE GIVEN IN THE 'N'     ZQ
)@@G@@@B@@@]             FIELD OF THE COMMAND CARDS.  @@@@@]@@@@@]@G@@@A      ZR
)@@G@@    L - PRINT ALL NO MATCH BLOCKS WHEN DOING A CMP ON DEMAND.     @@@@@]ZS
)@@G@@@@@@@]@E@@@]         NOTE:  O, A, H, AND X APPLY UNDER ALL CONDITIONS.  ZT
)@@G@@@E@@@]                F AND D OPTIONS ARE MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE.     @D@@@ ZU
)@@G@@                    P OPTIONS WORKS WITH CMP ONLY     @@@@@]@@@@@]@@@@@]ZV
)@@G@@@@@@@]@@@@@]@B@@@]    IV.  COPY-DUMP COMMANDS AVAILABLE     @@@@@]@@@@@]ZW
)@@G@@@G@@@]        THE  FOLLOWING  COPY-DUMP  COMMANDS ARE DESCRIBED UNDER THZX
)@@G@@E     @G@@@]    CONDITIONS PRESCRIBED BY EACH OF THE APPLICABLE OPTIONS.ZY
)@@G@@   SOME     @G@@@]    GENERAL  GUIDELINES  TO FOLLOW WHEN PREPARING COPYZZ
)@@G@@-DUMP COMMAND     @#@@@]    CARDS ARE:    @@@@@]@E@@@]       A.  A COPY-AA
)@@G@@DUMP COMMAND MAY START IN ANY COLUMN.     @@@@@]@G@@@]       B.    A  BLAB
)@@G@@ANK FOLLOWS THE COPY-DUMP COMMAND;  FILENAMES ARE     @ @@@]       SEPARAC
)@@G@@ATED BY COMMAS.   @@@@@]@E@@@]       C.  FILENAMES ARE 1-12 CHARACTER NAAD
)@@G@@MES FOR THE FILE. @@@@@]@F@@@]       D.  QUALIFIERS AND F-CYCLES ARE NOTAE
)@@G@@ RECOGNIZED BY THE COPY-@F@@@]       DUMP PROCESSOR BUT FILES NEEDING QUAF
)@@G@@ALIFIERS AND F-CYCLES   @F@@@]       IN THEIR NAMES MAY BE ACCESED THRU AG
)@@G@@@USE CONTROL CARDS.     @@@@@]@G@@@]       E.    PERIODS  ARE ALLOWED ASAH
)@@G@@ TERMINATORS FOR FILENAMES,  AS     @B@@@]       WELL AS WHEN ASSIGNING AI
)@@G@@THE FILE.   @@@@@]@ @@@]        COPY-DUMP COMMANDS    @@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]AJ
)@@G@@   1.  COMPARE:  CMP     FN1,FN1    @E@@@]                 CMP     FN1,FAK
)@@G@@N2,N      (F OPTION ONLY)     @@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]           A.  NO F OR DAL
)@@G@@ OPTION:    @F@@@]             COMPARE ONE FILE FROM TAPE FILENAME ONE TAM
)@@G@@O TAPE FILE-@F@@@]             NAME TWO. THE BLOCK AND RECORD COUNTS AREAN
)@@G@@ KEPT UP. IF@F@@@]             THE TWO TAPE FILES DO NOT COMPARE BOTH REAO
)@@G@@CORDS WILL  @G@@@]             BE PRINTED AND BOTH TAPES POSITIONED IMMEAP
)@@G@@DIATELY AFTER     @A@@@]             THE NEXT END-OF-FILE.  @@@@@]@^@@@]AQ
)@@G@@           B.  F OPTION:@G@@@]             COMPARE TAPE FILENAME ONE TO AR
)@@G@@TAPE FILENAME TWO FOR 'N'     @G@@@]             NUMBER  OF  FILES,   KEAS
)@@G@@EPING  UP WITH BLOCK AND RECORD     @G@@@]             COUNTS. IF THE TAAT
)@@G@@PES DO NOT COMPARE, BOTH RECORDS WILL     @G@@@]             BE PRINTED AU
)@@G@@AND BOTH TAPES POSITIONED IMMEDIATELY AFTER     @G@@@]             THE  AV
)@@G@@NEXT END-OF-FILE.   IF  'N'  NUMBER OF FILES HAVE     @G@@@]            AW
)@@G@@ NOT  YET BEEN COMPARED THE COMPARE OF THE NEXT FILE IS     @^@@@]      AX
)@@G@@       BEGUN.     @@@@@]@B@@@]           C.  D OPTION:  NOT IMPLEMENTED.AY
)@@G@@@@@@@]@F@@@A           D. _IN DEMAND, WITHOUT THE L OPTION, THE BLOCKS TAZ
)@@G@@HAT DO@C@@@A              NOT COMPARE WILL NOT BE PRINTED.  @@@@@]@A@@@]BA
)@@G@@   2.  DUPLICATE:  DUP   FN1,FN2    @A@@@]                   DUP   FN1,FBB
)@@G@@N2,N  @@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]           A.  NO F OR D OPTION:    @G@@@]      BC
)@@G@@       COPY  ONE  FILE  OR  'N'  NUMBER  OF RECORDS FROM TAPE     @G@@@]BD
)@@G@@             FILENAME ONE TO TAPE FILENAME TWO. AN END-OF-FILE MARK     BE
)@@G@@@G@@@]             IS  NOT AUTOMATICALLY WRITTEN TO THE SECOND TAPE.   IBF
)@@G@@F     @G@@@]             MORE  THAN  THE  CURRENT REEL OF OUTPUT IS REQUBG
)@@G@@IRED TO     @F@@@]             CONTAIN FN1, A NEW REEL MOUNT IS REQUESTEBH
)@@G@@D ON FN2.   @@@@@]@^@@@]           B.  F OPTION:@G@@@]             COPY BI
)@@G@@ 'N'  NUMBER  OF  FILES FROM TAPE FILENAME ONE TO     @G@@@]            BJ
)@@G@@ TAPE  FILENAME TWO.   ONE EOF IS AUTOMATICALLY WRITTEN     @G@@@]      BK
)@@G@@       BETWEEN  EACH  FILE,    WITH TWO WRITTEN FOLLOWING THE     @G@@@]BL
)@@G@@             LAST  FILE.    THE TAPE WILL BE POSITIONED BETWEEN THE     BM
)@@G@@@ @@@]             LAST TWO EOF'S.  @@@@@]@^@@@]           C.  D OPTION:BN
)@@G@@@G@@@]             COPY  ONE  FILE  OR  'N'  NUMBER  OF RECORDS FROM TAPBO
)@@G@@E     @G@@@]             FILENAME  ONE  TO  MASS STORAGE FILENAME TWO.  BP
)@@G@@ IF THE     @G@@@]             BLOCK  SIZE  IS NOT AN EVEN SECTOR MULTIPBQ
)@@G@@LE,  THE LAST     @G@@@]             SECTOR IS PADDED OUT WITH ZEROS.  NBR
)@@G@@OTE:  THIS DOES NOT     @G@@@]             WORK  IN REVERSE - A MASS-STOBS
)@@G@@RAGE FILE CANNOT BE DUPED     @^@@@]             TO TAPE.   @@@@@]@@@@@]BT
)@@G@@@^@@@]   3.  PRINT:  PRT   FN1@ @@@]               PRT   FN1,N    @C@@@]BU
)@@G@@               PRT   FN1,N1,N2   (D OPTION ONLY)@@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]      BV
)@@G@@     A.  NO F OR D OPTION:    @G@@@]             PRINT  THE  ENTIRE FILEBW
)@@G@@ OR PRINT 'N' NUMBER OF RECORDS     @F@@@]             ACCORDING  TO THEBX
)@@G@@ PRINT OPTIONS SPECIFIED (O,A,H,X). @@@@@]@^@@@]           B.  F OPTION:BY
)@@G@@@G@@@]             PRINT THE CONTENTS OF 'N' NUMBER OF FILES ACCORDING TBZ
)@@G@@O     @D@@@]             THE PRINT OPTIONS SPECIFIED (O,A,H,X).   @@@@@]CA
)@@G@@@^@@@]           C.  D OPTION:@@@@@]@B@@@]             1.  NO COUNTERS: CB
)@@G@@ PRT  FN1.  @G@@@]               START AT BEGINNING OF FILE AND PRINT ENCC
)@@G@@TIRE CONTENTS IN  @B@@@]               SECTOR (28 WORD) BLOCKS.   @C@@@]CD
)@@G@@             2.  FIRST COUNTER:  PRT  FN1.,N1   @D@@@]               PRICE

)@@G@@@ @@@]           A. NO D OPTION     @G@@@]             WRITE  AN  EOF MAEP
)@@G@@RK FOLLOWED BY 4096-WORD BLOCKS (3.36     @G@@@]             FT  ON  9  EQ
)@@G@@TRACK  TAPE)  OF  #CLEAR TO THE END-OF-TAPE     @G@@@]             MARKEER

)@@G@@ THE  END-OF-TAPE MARK.  THE TAPE IS THEN POSITIONED ON     @G@@@]      ET
)@@G@@       THE  DOWN-TAPE  SIDE  OF  THE  FIRST  END-OF-FILE MARK     @G@@@]EU

)@@G@@@G@@@]             THE  CHK  COMMAND.   BEFORE INITIATING THE OVW COMMANEW
)@@G@@D     @G@@@]             THE  TAPE SHOULD BE POSITIONED BETWEEN THE 2 EOEX
)@@G@@F MARKS     @G@@@]             TERMINATING THE USER'S LAST GOOD FILE ON EY
)@@G@@THE TAPE.  IT     @G@@@]             TAKES APPROXIMATELY 7 MINUTES WALL EZ
)@@G@@CLOCK TIME TO OVER-     @F@@@]             WRITE AN ENTIRE 9 TRACK HIGH FA
)@@G@@DENSITY 2400 FOOT TAPE. @@@@@]@^@@@]           B. D OPTION  @ @@@]      FB
)@@G@@       NOT IMPLEMENTED  @@@@@]@@@@@]@C@@@]   12.  CHECK AN OVERWRITTEN TFC

)@@G@@@G@@@]             TAPE  SHOULD  BE POSITIONED AT THE FIRST BLOCK OF DATFF
)@@G@@A     @G@@@]             BEFORE  INITIATING  THE  COMMAND.   AFTER A SUCFG

)@@G@@EEN THE 2 EOF     @E@@@]             MARKS WHICH TERMINATE THE #CLEAR BLFI

)@@G@@    V. EXAMPLE OF A RUNSTREAM USING COPY-DUMP   @@@@@]@A@@@]            FR
)@@G@@       GENERAL SETUP    @@@@@]@#@@@]              @RUN@#@@@]            FS
)@@G@@  @HDG@G@@@]              @ASG,T     FILENAME     . MAY BE ANY ALPHAMERIFT
)@@G@@C NAME UP TO@H@@@]                                      . 12 CHARACTERS.FU
)@@G@@ NUMBERS AS WELL AS     @G@@@]                                      . LEFV
)@@G@@TTERS CAN START THE NAME.     @D@@@]              @CPD,OPTIONS          FW
)@@G@@  . NO BLANKS     @G@@@]              COPY-DUMP COMMAND CARDS . BLANKS FFX
)@@G@@OLLOWING COMMAND, COMMA @G@@@]                 EXAMPLE:             . BEFY
)@@G@@TWEEN SPECIFICATION FIELDS    @F@@@]                 PRT     FN1,5      FZ
)@@G@@  . COMMENT MAY FOLLOW HERE   @#@@@]              @FIN@@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]GA
)@@G@@                   SPECIFIC EXAMPLE @@@@@]@#@@@]              @RUN@#@@@]GB
)@@G@@              @HDG@B@@@]              @ASG,T     FN1,8C9,UNNNN    @A@@@]GC
)@@G@@              @ASG,C     FN2,8C9    @F@@@]              @CPD,F          GD
)@@G@@         . FILES OPTION SPECIFIED   @D@@@]              DUP     FN1,FN2,GE
)@@G@@3        . DUPE 3 FILES @D@@@]              TRW     FN1,FN2          . RGF
)@@G@@EWIND TAPES @E@@@]              CMP     FN1,FN2,3        . COMPARE 3 FILGG
)@@G@@ES    @ @@@]              TRW     FN1,FN2 @F@@@]              @CPD      GH
)@@G@@               . INITIALIZE CPD WITHOUT F @F@@@]              PRT     FNGI
)@@G@@2,5            . PRINT FIRST 5 RECORDS    @E@@@]              PSE     FNGJ
)@@G@@2              . GO TO END OF FILE  @E@@@]              PSB     FN2,5   GK
)@@G@@         . BACKUP 5 RECORDS   @F@@@]              PRT     FN2,5         GL
)@@G@@   . FILE 1 LAST 5 RECORDS    @G@@@]              @FREE,I     FN2       GM
)@@G@@   . I OPTION INHIBITS CATALOGING   @#@@@]              @FIN@@@@@]@@@@@]GN
)@@G@@@@@@@]@@@@@]@@@@@]@@@@@]@A@@@]    VI. RESTRICTIONS AND METHODOLOGY@@@@@]GO
)@@G@@@@@@@]@F@@@]         1.  ALL FILES MUST BE ASSIGNED PRIOR TO CALLING @CPGP
)@@G@@D.    @@@@@]@G@@@]         2.  NO MORE THAN THREE (3) TAPES (DUE TO SOI GQ
)@@G@@RESTRICTIONS)     @G@@@]         MAY  BE  ASSIGNED AT ONE TIME.   THESE GR
)@@G@@MAY BE SEVEN AND/OR     @ @@@]         NINE TRACK TAPES.    @@@@@]@G@@@]GS
)@@G@@         3  COPY-DUMP COMMAND CARDS ARE CHECKED FOR VALIDITY BEFORE     GT
)@@G@@@G@@@]         EXECUTING THE COMMAND.  IF AN INVALID COMMAND IS FOUND, AGU
)@@G@@N     @G@@@]         ERROR MESSAGE IS PRINTED OUT.   A LISTING IS THEN PGV
)@@G@@RODUCED     @G@@@]         OF  ANY  OTHER  COPY-DUMP  COMMANDS,   BUT  TGW
)@@G@@HESE  ARE NOT     @G@@@]         EXECUTED.    THIS  LISTING  IS  TERMINAGX
)@@G@@TED  BY  READING  A     @F@@@]         NON-COPY-DUMP COMMAND.  BLANK COMGY
)@@G@@MAND CARDS ARE IGNORED. @@@@@]@G@@@]         4.    A  USER  CAN  SPECIFYGZ
)@@G@@  HIS  PRINTOUT  TO  BE  IN ANY     @G@@@]         COMBINATION  OF  PRINHA
)@@G@@T  FORMATS.    OCTAL  IS  THE DEFAULT     @G@@@]         FORMAT.    ANY HB
)@@G@@ RECORDS  PRINTED ARE PRINTED ONCE FOR EACH     @G@@@]         REQUESTEDHC
)@@G@@  FORMAT.    IF  THE  O,   A,  AND H OPTIONS WERE     @F@@@]         SPEHD
)@@G@@CIFIED, EACH RECORD WOULD BE PRINTED THREE TIMES.     @@@@@]@G@@@]      HE
)@@G@@   5.  AN END-OF-FILE IS COUNTED AS A RECORD IN THE EXECUTION     @G@@@]HF
)@@G@@         OF  A COMMAND.   HOWEVER IT IS NOT COPIED USING DUP EXCEPT     HG
)@@G@@@F@@@]         UNDER 'F' OPTION CONTROL.  (SEE DUPLICATE FUNCTION.)     HH
)@@G@@@@@@@]@G@@@]         6.  WITHOUT THE 'F' OPTION EACH COMMAND CARD SPECIFHI
)@@G@@IES THE     @G@@@]         ACTION REQUIRED ON A PARTICULAR FILE TO THE NHJ
)@@G@@EXT EOF MARK.     @F@@@]         ADDITIONAL   COMMAND   CARDS   ARE  NECHK
)@@G@@ESSARY  TO  ACCESS@A@@@]         ADDITIONAL FILES ON A TAPE.@@@@@]@@@@@]HL
)@@G@@@G@@@]         CAUTION:   WHEN PRINTING A TAPE, ENOUGH COMMANDS SHOULD BHM
)@@G@@E     @G@@@]         INCLUDED TO ACCESS ALL EXPECTED EOF'S.  THIS MAY REHN
)@@G@@SULT IN     @E@@@]         PRINTING INFORMATION OF UNKNOWN CLASSIFICATIOHO
)@@G@@N.    @@@@@]@@@@@]@G@@@]           7.    A PRT OF A DRUM FILE WILL ALWAYHP
)@@G@@S ACCESS THE ENTIRE     @G@@@]         CONTENTS  OF  THE  HIGHEST  TRACKHQ
)@@G@@  REFERENCED  WITHIN THIS     @G@@@]         ASSIGNMENT, EVEN THOUGH THEHR
)@@G@@ USER MAY NOT HAVE WRITTEN INTO     @G@@@]         ALL SECTORS OF THAT THS
)@@G@@RACK.  THE EOF STATUS RETURN WILL NOT     @G@@@]         OCCUR  UNTIL  AHT
)@@G@@N ATTEMPT IS MADE TO ACCESS THE NEXT TRACK.     @F@@@]         THIS  MAYHU
)@@G@@  RESULT  IN  PRINTING  INFORMATION  OF  UNKNOWN@^@@@]         CLASSIFICHV
)@@G@@ATION.@@@@@]@@@@@]@G@@@]         8.   WHEN  CHANGING  BLOCK  SIZES  UNDEHW
)@@G@@R  THE  'D' OPTION,     @G@@@]         INCREMENTATION SHOULD BE IN POWERHX
)@@G@@S OF 2 (I.E.  BLOCK SIZES     @G@@@]         OF  2,4,8,16,32,64,  ETC.) HY
)@@G@@TO PRINT THE ENTIRE DRUM SPACE.     @G@@@]         AN  ODD  MULTIPLE WILHZ
)@@G@@L RESULT IN AN EOF RETURN IN THE LAST     @G@@@]         BLOCK  OF  THE IA
)@@G@@ HIGHEST  TRACK SINCE IT WILL NOT FALL ON A     @^@@@]         TRACK BOUIB
)@@G@@NDARY.@@@@@]@G@@@]         9.   COMMENTS ARE ALLOWED ON COMMAND CARDS.  IC
)@@G@@ THEY WILL BE     @G@@@]         PRINTED  OUT  ON  THE USER'S LISTING,  ID
)@@G@@BUT WILL BE IGNORED     @G@@@]         DURING  EXECUTION  OF  THE  COMMAIE
)@@G@@ND.    A  COMMENT MUST BE     @G@@@]         PRECEEDED BY A BLANK PERIODIF
)@@G@@ BLANK (' .  ') WHICH MAY START     @G@@@]         IN  ANY  COLUMN  AFTEIG
)@@G@@R  THE  LAST  REQUIRED  COMMAND  CARD     @D@@@]         INFORMATION ANDIH
)@@G@@ MAY EXTEND TO COLUMN 80.     @@@@@]@G@@@]         10.    CPD WILL HANDLII
)@@G@@E TAPES THAT DO NOT HAVE 6 CHARACTERS     @G@@@]         IN  THE  LAST  IJ
)@@G@@WORD  OF  A BLOCK (SUCH AS A CARD IMAGE BCD     @G@@@]         TAPE)  ANIK
)@@G@@D  WILL  INFORM  YOU  WHEN THIS SITUATION OCCURS.     @G@@@]         WHEIL
)@@G@@N DUPING SUCH A TAPE,  THE LAST WORD WILL BE PADDED OUT     @G@@@]      IM
)@@G@@   WITH  ZEROES.    A TAPE OF THIS TYPE SHOULD BE DUPED USING     @F@@@]IN
)@@G@@         CPD   BEFORE   ACCESS  IS  ATTEMPTED  WITH  OTHER  SYSTEM@^@@@]IO
)@@G@@         PROCESSORS.    @@@@@]@G@@@]         11.   THE  HIGHEST TRACK REIP
)@@G@@FERENCED IN A MASS-STORAGE FILE     @G@@@]         MAY BE DETERMINED BY IQ
)@@G@@DOING A 'PSF' OR A 'PSE'.   THE TRACK     @G@@@]         NUMBER RETURNEDIR
)@@G@@ WILL BE ONE LESS THAN THE ACTUAL NUMBER OF     @G@@@]         TRACKS,  IS
)@@G@@ SINCE  THE FIRST TRACK IS CONSIDERED TO BE TRACK     @#@@@]         ZERIT

)@@G@@  A2,9              . 4TH CHAR                       BPD 3H @H@4@0      YQ
)@@G@@    TNE       A1,A2             .                                BPD 3H YR
)@@G@@@H@@@4          TNE       A8,A2             .                           YS
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@3@0          J         LOC80             .               YT
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@3          LMJ       X5,LOC80          .   YU
)@@G@@                              BPD 3H@H@@@0          AX,U      X4,1      YV
)@@G@@        .                                BPD 3H @H@@@0          JGD     YW
)@@G@@  R5,LOC75          .                                BPD 3H @H@3@0      YX
)@@G@@    J         LOC70             . NO MATCH                       BPD 3H YY
)@@G@@@H@@@3          J         0,X5              . NO MATCH                  YZ
)@@G@@      BPD 3H@H@@@0LOC80  .                                              ZA
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          AA,U      A6,9              .   ZB
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @H@@@0LOC81    .                    ZC
)@@G@@                                         BPD 3H @H@@@0          AA,U    ZD
)@@G@@  A6,9              .                                BPD 3H @H@@@0LOC82 ZE
)@@G@@.                                                                BPD 3H ZF
)@@G@@@H@@@0          AA,U      A6,9              .                           ZG
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0LOC85  .                                              ZH
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          DL        A3,BLOCK,X4       . GEZI
)@@G@@T VALUE                      BPD 3H @H@@@0          S,T3      A6,$+1    ZJ
)@@G@@        . SHIFT                          BPD 3H @H@@@0          LDSL    ZK
)@@G@@  A3,0              . SHIFT OUT FIRST PART OF VALUE  BPD 3H @H@@@0      ZL
)@@G@@    LA        A5,BLOCK+2,X4     .                                BPD 3H ZM
)@@G@@@H@@@0          S,T3      A6,$+1            .                           ZN
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0          SSL       A4,0              .               ZO
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          S,T3      A6,$+1            .   ZP
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @H@@@0          LDSL      A4,0      ZQ
)@@G@@        . VALUE IN A3,A4                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          J       ZR
)@@G@@  LOC90             .                                BPD 3H @H@@@0LOC88 ZS
)@@G@@ .                                                               BPD 3H ZT
)@@G@@@H@@@0          DL        A3,BLOCK,X4       .                           ZU
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0LOC90  .                                              ZV
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@4          SZ        A6                .   ZW
)@@G@@                              BPD 3H@H@@@0          LA,U      A1,0110   ZX
)@@G@@        . 72 BITS                        BPD 3H @H@@@0          AN      ZY
)@@G@@  A1,SAVEX2         .                                BPD 3H @H@@@0      ZZ
)@@G@@    S,T3      A1,$+1            .                                BPD 3H AA
)@@G@@@H@@@0          DSL       A3,0              .                           AB
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0          S,T3      A1,$+1            .               AC
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          LDSL      A3,0              .   AD
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @H@@@0          DTE       A3,HOLD   AE
)@@G@@        . EQUAL                          BPD 3H @H@4@0          J       AF
)@@G@@  LOC70             . NO MATCH                       BPD 3H @H@@@4      AG
)@@G@@    J         0,X5             . NO MATCH                       BPD 3H  AH
)@@G@@@H@@@0          J         LOC45             . MATCH - PRINT MESSAGE     AI
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0.                                                     AJ
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0-868,868                                  AK
)@@G@@                              BPD 3H@H@@@0          LMJ       X11,DREAD AL
)@@G@@        . READ DISC                       BPD 3H@H@@@0DFN1      +       AM
)@@G@@  00                .                                 BPD 3H@H@@@0      AN
)@@G@@    +         00                .                                 BPD 3HAO
)@@G@@@H@@@0          +         0,BLOCK           . BUFFER                    AP
)@@G@@      BPD 3H@H@@@0          +         CDIMGE            . EOF ADDRESS   AQ
)@@G@@                  BPD 3H@H@@@0-964,964                                  AR
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @H@@@0NOCOMM   EQU  15   . NUMBER OFAS
)@@G@@ COMMANDS                                 BPD 3H@H@@@0HOLD  RES  5  . WOAT
)@@G@@RDS 1 & 2 - SEARCH VALUE, WORD 3 - TEMP WORK AREA    BPD 3H @H@@@0-990  AU
)@@G@@                                                                 BPD 3H AV
)@@G@@@H@@@0           +  'LOC',SEARCH       . SEARCH COMMAND                 AW
)@@G@@      BPD 3H@H@@@0-1000,1000                                            AX
)@@G@@                  BPD 3H@H@@@0NOCMP  P  3,17,NOCOMP    .                AY
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @H@@@0-1059                         AZ
)@@G@@                                         BPD 3H @H@@@0FDIT  'FOUND AT OCBA
)@@G@@TAL WORD **        '  .                              BPD 3H @H@@@0-1070 BB
)@@G@@                                                                 BPD 3H BC
)@@G@@@H@@@0    ' OCTAL WORD '                                                BD
)@@G@@      BPD 3H@H@@@0OCTCNT  +  '      '  .                                BE
)@@G@@                  BPD 3H@H@@@0@ASM,E   CPD.SIGN/03G,CPD.SIGN/3H,CPD.SIGNBF
)@@G@@/3H                           BPD 3H@H@@@0-119,119                      BG
)@@G@@                                          BPD 3H@H@@@0SIG  'BPD/CPD 3H 'BH
)@@G@@   . SIGNATURE PACKET                                 BPD 3H@H@@@0@ASM,EBI
)@@G@@    CPD.DRUM/CPD,CPD.DRUM/3H,CPD.DRUM/3H                          BPD 3HBJ
)@@G@@@H@@@0-53                                                               BK
)@@G@@      BPD 3H@H@@@0          SX        X11,SAVEX11       . SAVE RETURN ADBL
)@@G@@DRESS             BPD 3H@I@@@0          DL        A0,0,X11          . GEBM
)@@G@@T FILE NAME                   . BPD 3H    @H@@@0          DS        A0,DBN
)@@G@@RPKT          . STORE IN I/O PKT                BPD 3H@H@@@0          DSBO
)@@G@@        A0,FITEM          . STORE IN FITME PKT              BPD 3H@H@@@0BP
)@@G@@          LA        A0,2,X11          . BUFFER ADDRESS                  BQ
)@@G@@BPD 3H@H@@@0          SA,H2     A0,DRPKT+4        .                     BR

)@@G@@  . SAVE POINTER FOR DISC CMP      BPD 3H @H@@@0-61,62                  BU
)@@G@@                                                BPD 3H@H@@@0-85,86      BV
)@@G@@                                                            BPD 3H@H@@@0BW
)@@G@@-119,119                                                                BX

)@@G@@                        BPD 3H@H@@@0          LX        X11,SAVEX11     CA
)@@G@@  . GET RETURN ADDRESS              BPD 3H@H@@@0          J         4,X1CB
)@@G@@1             .                                 BPD 3H@H@@@0-143,143    CC
)@@G@@                                                            BPD 3H@H@@@0CD
)@@G@@          LX        X11,SAVEX11       .                                 CE
)@@G@@BPD 3H@H@@@0          LA        A0,3,X11          . GET EOF ADDRESS     CF

)@@G@@                                    BPD 3H@H@@@0SAVEX11  00  . HOLD X11 CI
)@@G@@                                                BPD 3H@A@@@0@COPY,R CPD.CJ
)@@G@@CPD/3H,TPF$.CPD/CPD     @A@@@0@COPY,R CPD.CONVERSION/CPD,TPF$.    @A@@@0CK
)@@G@@@COPY,R CPD.DRUM/3H,TPF$.DRUM/CPD   @A@@@0@COPY,R CPD.TPRD$/03F,TPF$.TPRCL
)@@G@@D$/CPD@A@@@0@COPY,R CPD.SIGN/3H,TPF$.SIGN/CPD   @A@@@0@COPY,R CPD.PRT/03CM
)@@G@@E,TPF$.PRT/CPD    @ @@@0@COPY,R CPD.SCAN/CPD,TPF$.    @ @@@0@COPY,S CPD.CN
)@@G@@CPDPROCS/CPD,TPF$.@]@@@0@MAP ,.CPD  @^@@@0@ADD CPD.CPDMAP/CPD     @^@@@0CO
)@@G@@@COPY,A  .CPD,CPD.CPD   ___  BPD 3H @H@@@0          SLJ       GENRD1    CP
)@@G@@        . READ BLOCK          BPD 3H@H@@@0          DS        A0,DFN1   CQ
)@@G@@        . DISC FILE NAME                  BPD 3H@H@@@0-397,397          CR
)@@G@@                                                     BPD 3H @H@@@0BPDA1 CS
)@@G@@.                                                                BPD 3H CT
)@@G@@@H@@@0          TZ,H1     OPTION2           . 'Q' OR 'R' OPTIONS SET ?  CU
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0-595,595                                              CV
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          TZ,S4     OPTION            . L CW
)@@G@@OPTION                       BPD 3H @H@@@0-609                          CX
)@@G@@                                         BPD 3H @H@@@0          LA      CY
)@@G@@  A2,A3             . GET OCTAL CNT                  BPD 3H @H@@@0      CZ
)@@G@@    SLJ       OCTPT             . SET UP OCTAL VALUE             BPD 3H DA
)@@G@@@H@@@0          SA        A1,OCTCNT         . STORE                     DB
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0-615,617                                              DC
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0-645                                      DD
)@@G@@                             BPD 3H @^@@@0OCTPT*    NOP       .   @B@@@0DE
)@@G@@          LA        A1,('666666')     .   @D@@@0          LSSL      A2,1DF
)@@G@@8             . USE RIGHT HALF@B@@@0          LR,U      R2,4            DG
)@@G@@ .    @]@@@0GOFOCT   .  @B@@@0          LDSL      A1,3              .   DH
)@@G@@@B@@@0          LSSC      A1,3              .   @B@@@0          JGD     DI
)@@G@@  R2,GOFOCT         .   @B@@@0          LDSL      A1,3              .   DJ
)@@G@@@B@@@0          J         *OCTPT            .   @H@@@0/ . SEARCH FOR A FDK
)@@G@@IELD - MAX OF 12 CHAR                                 BPD 3H@H@@@0SEARCHDL
)@@G@@ .                                                               BPD 3H DM
)@@G@@@H@@@0          DL        A0,FILEN          . GET FILE NAME             DN
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0          DS        A0,FN1            . STORE IN I/O PDO
)@@G@@KT               BPD 3H @H@@@0          DS        A0,DFN1           . STDP
)@@G@@ORE IN I/O PKT               BPD 3H @H@@@0          GETFLD    SAMECD    DQ
)@@G@@        . GET SEARCH VALUE               BPD 3H @H@@@0          JZ      DR
)@@G@@  A2,BADCOM         . NO VALUE                       BPD 3H @H@@@0      DS
)@@G@@    SA        A2,SAVEX2         . SAVE # CHARS                   BPD 3H DT
)@@G@@@H@@@0          TZ        OPTION2           . Q OR R OPTION SET ?       DU
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0          J         LOC60             . YES 9 BIT MODEDV
)@@G@@                 BPD 3H @H@@@0          MSI,U     A2,6              . CODW
)@@G@@MVERT TO BITS                BPD 3H @H@@@0          SA        A2,HOLD+2 DX
)@@G@@        .                                BPD 3H @H@@@0          L,U     DY
)@@G@@  A2,0110           . SUB FROM 72 BITS               BPD 3H @H@@@0      DZ
)@@G@@    AN        A2,HOLD+2         . GET # BITS TO SHIFT            BPD 3H EA
)@@G@@@H@@@0          S,T3      A2,$+1            . STORE IN NEXT COMMAND     EB
)@@G@@     BPD 3H @H@@@0          LDSL      A0,0              . ZERO FILL VALUEC
)@@G@@E                BPD 3H @H@@@0          DS        A0,HOLD          . SAVED
